HEADWORD: Desponsage
<hw>De*spon"sage</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From L.
<ets>desponsus</ets>, p. p. See <er>Despond</er>.]</ety>
<def>Betrothal.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ethelbert . . . went peaceably to King Offa for
<qex>desponsage</qex> of Athilrid, his daughter.</q>
<rj><qau>Foxe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Desponsate</ent>⟦br⟧
